---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About — VitalCalc"
	description="VitalCalc is a free, private, browser-based BMI calculator. Learn how it works and why it's free."
	canonicalPath="/about"
>
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-[#2B2013]">About VitalCalc</h1>
	<div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-[#5C4F3D]">
		<p>
			VitalCalc is a single, focused tool: calculating your Body Mass Index
			(BMI) from your height and weight, and showing where that number
			falls on the World Health Organization's standard weight
			categories. Everything runs entirely in your web browser &mdash;
			no data you enter is ever sent to a server.
		</p>
		<p>
			Because there is no server-side processing or account system,
			VitalCalc can stay completely free with no sign-up, no watermark,
			and no usage limits. The site is supported by on-page advertising.
		</p>
		<p>
			BMI is a quick, population-level screening measure, not a medical
			diagnosis. It doesn't account for muscle mass, bone density, age,
			sex, or fat distribution. Always talk to a doctor or healthcare
			provider for a full assessment of your health.
		</p>
	</div>
</Layout>
